# TypeScript

- Prefer `const`; use `let` only when reassigned. Avoid `var`.
- Enable and respect strict compiler options when the project uses them; avoid `any` unless justified.
- Model external data with explicit types or validation (e.g. zod) at boundaries.
- Use async/await consistently; handle rejections; avoid floating promises.
- Colocate types with modules; export only what consumers need.
